>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text of Giustolisi as reported in SEG\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Giustolisi proposed that it was a dedication to or invovation of the divinity Silenos, but Manganaro, and Moretti (comm in SEG) instead suggest that it is a funerary aedicola for two men called Silenos, perhaps father and son, with the designation as heroes agathoi, as is common in the later Hellenistic period.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 36.0854 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Giustolisi 1981 121-122 figs.144-148r \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001947\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001947\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1992 500-501 no.IX \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001830\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001830\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[194,197,200,203,206,209,212,215],{"id":195,"html":196},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\">http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan 